headline: Kyndryl Stock Drops 55%. It’s So Much Worse Than an Earnings Miss.
summary: Kyndryl Holdings  stock plummeted on Monday after the company announced the immediate departures of chief financial officer and general counsel.  CFO David Wyshner and General Counsel Edward Sebold vacated their positions, the company said.  Kyndryl shares sank 55% to $10.59, the largest single-day percent decrease on record, according to Dow Jones Market Data.
